deck: Mara Williams aka Rush is a member of the Legion Academy. She was transformed genetically by the Dominators to accelerate her speed to superhuman levels.
description:
Creation

Mara W. Williams is a character who appeared in Legion of Superheroes #51, "A Lil Legion Adventure" December 1993. She was created by Tom McCraw and Mike McAvennie.

Origin

Mara Wallace Williams was a supporting character in Legion of Super-Heroes. She was a young woman who had been abducted and genetically experimented upon by the Dominators. The spliced her genes with genetic material from the Tornado Twins Dawn and Don Allen, giving her super speed. After being found and liberated, she soon lived on the hospital planet Quarantine, where she made friends with former Legionnaire Kent Shakespeare and Celeste McCauley.

After an attempted jailbreak on Takron-Galtos, Cocheta Drisden is sent to Quarantine, where Kent Shakespeare and Celeste McCauley have been staying. Mara was one of the many genetically altered United Planets citizens that had been operated on to change their genetic makeups. While having an intimate conversation about her situation with Celeste, Grimbor attacked Quarantine in an attempt to rescue his daughter, Cocheta.

However, Mara joined up with Celeste to find out why the alarms at the medical facility were going off. They discovered Kent chained up and unconscious. Grimbor and the two get into a quick skirmish as he easily imprisons both of them in a few of his specialized traps. Soon the young children with super-powers that also live at Quarantine help Mara, Kent and Celeste get free and Grimbor is defeated.

Later Mara joined the Legion Academy and adopted the code name Rush. There she learned how to better use her powers and started using staff energy weapons.

Mara was wiped out by Zero Hour along with most of the character's of that timeline.

Powers and Abilities

She was transformed genetically by the Dominators to accelerate her speed to superhuman levels. It is not known for how long she can act at optimal speeds before tiring. The flaw in her abilities was that she could not naturally decelerate, her body always being in hyper-speed. However she was given a Vibration Stabilizer device which would allow her to move at normal human speed without need of concentration.
name: Rush

deck: Server Aja is the daughter of a billionaire industrialist. Once the technophile Zhang discovered she had metahuman abilities she acquired extensive cybernetic implants.
description:
Current Events

Server Aja has not been seen since the defeat of her master Kestrel in Teen Titans #28 - Legacy Part 2: Impure Thoughts in the Chaos Dimension. None of the post-battle pages shows what happened to Server Aja, which leaves her current state or whereabouts a complete unknown.

Origin

Zhang Xiaomei is the privileged daughter of a former Chinese national who made billions exporting cheap labour to Western industrialists. Zhang is obsessed with a life in the electronic world, and has acquired extensive cybernetic implants to augment her inborn metahuman abilities. She took the name Server Aja upon joining a group of young metahuman criminals who were all from similar wealthy backgrounds.

Creation

Server Aja was created by writer Gail Simone and artist Rob Liefeld in 2005. Their issues of Teen Titans are (as of 2015) the only issues in which Server Aja has appeared.

Server Aja is visually very similar to Void, a character that played a prominent role in the WildC.A.T.s comics by Wildstorm. Wildstorm became a publishing imprint of DC Comics in 1999 and was shut down in 2010.

Major Story Arcs

Server Aja makes her first appearance in Teen Titans #27 - Legacy Part 1. Server Aja and her allies are in the middle of a failed heist turned hostage situation when the Teen Titans intervene, and defeat them. Server Aja reveals that they chose that specific day to commit their crime because it was Father's Day, suggesting that the involved metahumans all had issues with their wealthy fathers. When the police van transporting them to prison is attacked by Kestrel - a servant of the Lords and Agents of Chaos - he offers two of the metahumans the chance to be his minions, implying that the other two must be killed. After a brief battle Server Aja and Cross Christina emerge from the police van. They then engage the Teen Titans once more, revealing that the power imbued by Kestrel has turned them into his slaves.

In Teen Titans #28 - Legacy Part 2: Impure Thoughts the Teen Titans follow Kestrel to the Chaos Dimension. Sitting at the feet of Kestrel's throne, a stammering Server Aja announces that the Titans have arrived, which leads Cross Christina to suggests that Kestrel's gift of power 'broke her mind'. During the battle with the Teen Titans Cross Christina betrays Kestrel, allowing the Teen Titans to win the day. What happens to Server Aja is left unknown.
name: Server Aja

Creation

Kevin Mondell is an AC Comic's character. Created by she first appears in Venture Venture #1 released in 1986. Many of the details of the character when first introduced in the series were never followed any further. Unfortunately the story line of the team was never followed as A.C Comics stopped its publication.

Origin

Explorers, Ltd. Kevin Mondell, Stacey Williams, Fiona Page and Mike Nesmith are four super-powered heroes-for-hire just starting out.

Explorers, Ltd. balk at their employers’ demands that they act like respectable superheroes, while interpersonal tensions on the team begin to strain. This is no time to have to face a couple of supremely-powerful mystical types, but that’s just what happens.

Characteristics and Appearance

Eyes: White (true color unknown)

Hair: Unknown

Height: 6'1"

Weight: Unknown

Identity: Secret Identity

Citizenship: New Orleans, United States

Occupation: Adventurer, Head of Explorers, Ltd

Marital Status: Single

Base Of Operations: New Orleans, United States of America

Relatives: None known

Powers and Abilities

The alien liquid which he had ingested has changed Kevin's physiology to superhuman levels. thereby rendering him virtually immortal, almost totally immune to disease or aging, and able to regenerate injured or missing body tissue. is impervious to most forms of damage and can absorb a tremendous amount of punishment without injury. He is unfazed by blows delivered from opponents weaker than he and can withstand blows even by those who are stronger, though continuous and repeated hits by opponents of such great strength can eventually wear him down.

Equipment

Kevin Mondell has in his possession a technologically advanced helmet. A part of the Commander's appearance, he is rarely seen without his red helmet. Technology wired into the inside of the helmet allows him specific attributes both physically and psychologically. The helmet enhances his strength, allowing him to lift tons of weight without exerting himself, he has displayed in the past lifting a teammates while still being able to fly. The helmet is highly durable, withstanding bullets without losing its integrity.

These portals allow her to pass instantly into apparently any dimension she has desired, at times having several opening and closing at various times and places. She become the "Exit" in most of her missions, being able to instantly leave a dire situation. As far as distance can be understood when opening or closing one of her portals by her powers they don't seem to have any, being able to open portals on our world or into other cross dimensional planes.

description:
Creation

Stacey Williams is an AC Comic's character. Created by she first appears in Venture Venture #1 released in 1986. Many of the details of the character when first introduced in the series were never followed any further. Unfortunately the story line of the team was never followed as A.C Comics stopped its publication.

Origin

Stacey was a cheerleader, an otherwise a young normal teenager girl living a normal life. Than there was the accident and Stacey's normal life would come to a halt, former changing it to a new normal. Stacy was now disabled and unable to ever walk again. However fate would change her life once again, now Stacey would not only walk again but also fly the skies.

Stacey would be recruited by a mysterious and sophisticated computer by the name of Zeus. She was made a clandestine offer by Zeus, join her and be gifted with great abilities. However she would have to be one of his agents and come to his service once she was called upon. She would be given a highly advanced computerized micro-suit that enables her to tap into the wide variety of the light spectrum. It also restored the function of her legs allowing her to walk again. Zeus is the true power behind her suit, it is Zeus who regulates its energy levels adjusting to either Stacey's requests for increase in its power levels for use. Stacy could now communicate with Zeus and she could request its vast records to inform her of various inquiries as the situation arose. Without the suit and its enhances. In fact without the suit Stacey would continue in her former state as disabled and unable to walk. Stacey agreed and has never looked back again.

History

The fiery Stacey later joined as partner of the team calling itself Explorers Ltd, a small group of super powered or technology based characters who united to use their individual abilities to assist in the exploration of the unknown, unexplained happenings on other worlds and dimensions. Explorers, Ltd. consisted other partner's named Kevin Mondell, Fiona Page and Mike Nesmith. These four super-powered explorers of the unknown for-hire.

Explorers, Ltd. balk at their employers’ demands that they act like respectable superheroes, while interpersonal tensions on the team begin to strain. This is no time to have to face a couple of supremely-powerful mystical types, but that’s just what happens.

Characteristics and Appearance

Eyes: Blue

Hair: Blond

Height: 5'7"

Weight: Unknown

Identity: Secret Identity

Citizenship: New Orleans, United States

Occupation: Adventurer, partner of Explorer, Ltd, Former student, cheerleader

Marital Status: Single

Base Of Operations: New Orleans, United States of America

Relatives: None known

Powers and Abilities

Equipment

Stacey Williams has the possesses a computerized micro power-suit.

Power Suit

Stacey employs a highly advanced computerized micro-suit that enables her to tap into the wide variety of the light spectrum's. The technology installed into her suit than enables her to fire pulse rays of heat or blasts light from her hands. She can also the shot to a tight beam able to pierce steel or change it to cause a wider impact. Stacy can use this ability to produce blinding flashes of light capable of affecting natural and mechanical vision. Stacey can also turn the energy into the ability of flight and is able to reach high altitudes at a fast rate. A glowing beam flows after her as she flies.

Stacey is otherwise a normal human without the suit and its enhances. In fact without the suit Stacey would continue in her former state as disabled.

A sophisticated computer by the name of Zeus is the true power behind her suit, it is Zeus who regulates its energy levels adjusting to either Stacey's requests for increase in its allotment for use. Stacy repeatedly uses Zeus's records to inform her of various inquiries as the situation is needed as it possessed vast knowledge. Stacy also possesses a limited and vague understanding of Zeus's technology, Zeus is also shown as being able to hack in to nigh-any computer system it has encountered.

deck: Cross Christina is a reckless metahuman with severe 'daddy issues'. Though she comes from a wealthy background she engages in criminal activity on Father's Day to make a point to her father.
description:
Current Events

Cross Christina has not been seen since the defeat of her master Kestrel in Teen Titans #28 - Legacy Part 2: Impure Thoughts in the Chaos Dimension. Her current whereabouts (as of 2015) are unknown.

Creation

Cross Christina was created by writer Gail Simone and artist Rob Liefeld in 2005. Their issues of Teen Titans are (as of 2015) the only issues in which Cross Christina has appeared.

Major Story Arcs

Cross Christina makes her first appearance in Teen Titans #27 - Legacy Part 1. Cross Christina and her metahuman allies are in the middle of a failed heist turned hostage situation when the Teen Titans intervene, and defeat them. When the police van transporting them to prison is attacked by Kestrel - a servant of the Lords and Agents of Chaos - he offers two of the metahumans the chance to be his minions, implying that the other two must be killed. After a brief battle Cross Christina and Server Aja emerge from the police van. They then engage the Teen Titans once more, revealing that the power imbued by Kestrel has turned them into his thralls.

In Teen Titans #28 - Legacy Part 2: Impure Thoughts the Teen Titans follow Kestrel to the Chaos Dimension, where he is holding the soul of Raven captive. During the battle that ensues Cross Christina is threatened by an angry Wonder Girl, which prompts her to betray her new master. She laughingly tells a shocked Kestrel she has always had 'daddy issues'. Although she helped the Teen Titans win the day, Cross Christina made it clear she was no friend of theirs. What happened to her is left unknown.
